Introduce two distinct protocol creation modes within the Protocol Builder:

Guided Protocol Mode (default)
Custom Protocol Mode (advanced)

Do not duplicate engines.
Do not separate into two independent tools.

Both modes must share the same validation and protocol engine.

==================================================
SECTION 1 — ADD MODE SELECTOR
==================================================

At the start of Protocol Builder, display:

Select Protocol Mode

Options:

Guided Protocol (Recommended)
Custom Protocol (Advanced)

Guided Protocol must be selected by default.

==================================================
SECTION 2 — GUIDED PROTOCOL MODE
==================================================

This mode uses validated protocol templates.

Workflow:

1. Enter Patient Data
2. Generate Recommended Protocol
3. Select Tempo
4. Load Timeline

System must:

Recommend one base protocol only.

==================================================
SECTION 3 — CUSTOM PROTOCOL MODE
==================================================

Allow manual protocol construction.

User must be able to:

Select peptides  
Define doses  
Define weeks  
Define escalation  
Add compounds  
Adjust monitoring  

All inputs must pass safety validation.

==================================================
SECTION 4 — SHARED VALIDATION ENGINE
==================================================

Both modes must use:

Safety Validation  
Contraindication Checks  
Monitoring Logic  
Economic Calculation  

Never bypass validation.

==================================================
SECTION 5 — ALLOW MODE CONVERSION
==================================================

Allow conversion:

Guided → Custom

User may modify recommended protocol manually.

==================================================
SECTION 6 — FINAL OBJECTIVE
==================================================

Provide two creation modes:

Guided for safety and simplicity  
Custom for flexibility and expertise  

Maintain a single unified protocol engine.